  "title": "Therapy Associate",
  "description": "<p>Are you passionate about helping others regain their independence and quality of life? Join our dynamic therapy team at Tan Tock Seng Hospital, where you'll play a vital role in transforming patients' lives through comprehensive rehabilitation care.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Partner with experienced therapists to deliver personalised patient care and implement therapy programmes </li><li>Prepare patients for treatment sessions with compassion and professionalism</li><li>Set up and maintain specialised therapy equipment to ensure optimal treatment delivery and safety standards </li><li>Supervise patients through prescribed exercises and therapy activities as instructed by the therapists</li><li>Assist with safe patient transfers and mobility support using proper techniques and equipment </li><li>Manage patient registration, appointment scheduling, and administrative support for smooth clinic operations </li><li>Maintain comprehensive equipment inventory, loan records, and workshop setup coordination</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma or GCE 'O' levels with relevant work experience</li><li>Genuine enthusiasm for helping people and making a meaningful difference in their lives</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills for effective patient interaction and team collaboration </li><li>Basic computer literacy for administrative tasks and patient management systems </li><li>Physical fitness and ability to safely handle patient transfers and mobility assistance</li><li>Healthcare experience preferred but not essential - training will be provided</li></ul><p><strong>Ready to Start Your Healthcare Career?</strong></p><p>Join us in delivering world-class rehabilitation care. We welcome both experienced candidates and those new to healthcare who are eager to learn and grow with us.</p><p><strong>Why Choose TTSH:</strong></p><ul><li>Comprehensive training and mentorship from experienced healthcare professionals in a supportive learning environment</li><li>Clear pathways for career advancement within Singapore's largest and most prestigious healthcare cluster </li><li>Exposure to various rehabilitation technologies, techniques, and evidence-based treatment approaches </li><li>Collaborative multidisciplinary team environment that values continuous learning and professional development </li><li>Competitive remuneration package with comprehensive healthcare benefits and staff privileges •</li><li>Meaningful opportunity to make a direct, positive impact on patients' recovery and quality of life</li></ul>",
